{
  "text": "Microdialysis samples were stored at \u03ea80\u00b0C until they were assayed for adenosine content using an RIA [CITATION_1] . Blood samples were centrifuged at 3,000 g for 10 min, and plasma was stored at \u03ea80\u00b0C until it was assayed for glycerol and free fatty acids (Sigma Chemical, St. Louis, MO).",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "25093057"
